{"title_page": "2018 in Ireland", "text_new": "{{For|Northern Ireland|2018 in Northern Ireland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{YearInIrelandNav|2018}}\n\nEvents during the year '''2018 in Ireland'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n[[File:Michael D. Higgins 2006.jpg|thumb|120px|upright|right|[[President of Ireland|President]] [[Michael D. Higgins]]]]\n* [[President of Ireland|President]]: [[Michael D. Higgins]] \n* [[Taoiseach]]: [[Leo Varadkar]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[T\u00e1naiste]]: [[Simon Coveney]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[Minister for Finance (Ireland)|Minister for Finance]]: [[Paschal Donohoe]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[Chief Justice of Ireland|Chief Justice]]: [[Frank Clarke (judge)|Frank Clarke]] \n* [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann|D\u00e1il]]: [[Members of the 32nd D\u00e1il|32nd]]\n* [[Seanad \u00c9ireann|Seanad]]: [[Members of the 25th Seanad|25th]]\n\n== Events ==\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n<!-- NOTE: Do not add national holidays (e.g Christmas, Easter) or anything that occurs every year (e.g Clocks go back) from this section -->\n\n=== January ===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 January \n**[[Teachta D\u00e1la|TDs]] rang in the [[2018|new year]] with a pay increase of \u20ac3,600, with a further increase to follow in October, bringing the total increase in 2018 to \u20ac4,500, yielding an annual salary of \u20ac94,500.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/happy-new-year-for-tds-who-wake-up-to-a-3600-pay-hike-36448456.html \"Happy new year for TDs - who wake up to a \u20ac3,600 pay hike\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-01.</ref>\n** The [[Road Safety Authority]] (RSA), published provisional statistics for 2017, which showed a 15% drop in road deaths compared with the previous year. A total of 158 people lost their lives on Ireland's roads compared to 186 lives lost in 2016. It represented 28 fewer fatalities on the previous year and was the lowest figure for annual road deaths since they were first officially recorded in 1959.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/breaking-news/irish-news/road-deaths-at-lowest-level-on-record-in-2017-36449405.html \"Road deaths at lowest level on record in 2017\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-02.</ref>\n* 2 January\n**A record 656 patients were on trolleys or on wards waiting for admission to a bed, according to the [[Irish Nurses and Midwives Organisation]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0102/930611-hospital-trolleys/ \"Record 656 patients waiting for hospital bed\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-02.</ref>\n**[[Met \u00c9ireann]] issued two Status Orange warnings as [[Storm Eleanor]] swept across the country bringing gusts of up to 130&nbsp;km/h and flooding in some areas. Up to 55,000 [[Electricity Supply Board|ESB]] customers in the west and north west of the country were left without power.<ref>[https://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/storm-eleanor-55000-esb-customers-without-power-amid-flooding-and-high-winds-821010.html Storm Eleanor: 55,000 ESB customers without power amid flooding and high winds], breakingnews.ie, 2018-01-02.</ref>\n* 3 January \u2013 The level of hospital overcrowding increased to a national record of 677 patients, according to the latest figures from the Irish Nurses and Midwives Organisation.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0103/930787-trolleys/ \"Hospital overcrowding increases to record level of 677 patients\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-03.</ref>\n* 4 January \u2013 [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]] apologised to patients who have experienced long delays and waits on trolleys in emergency departments as the [[Health Service Executive]] revealed that there were 12 children on trolleys in the three children's hospitals in [[Dublin]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/health/2018/0104/930977-hospital-overcrowding/  Taoiseach apologises to patients over emergency department delays], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-05.</ref>\n* 6 January \u2013 The [[diocese of Down and Connor]] suspended the [[Kiss of peace|sign of peace]] between people at mass in response to the surge in cases of influenza.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/religion-and-beliefs/diocese-bans-the-sign-of-peace-amid-australian-flu-fears-1.3347299 \"Diocese bans the \u2018sign of peace\u2019 amid Australian flu fears\"], ''[[The Irish Times]]'' (Dublin), 2018-01-06.</ref>\n* 7 January \u2013 Met \u00c9ireann issued a Status Orange low temperature warning for many counties, with temperatures plummeting to as low as -6C over night.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0107/931577-weather-warning/ Orange weather warning in place as temperatures plummet], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-07.</ref>\n* 8 January \u2013 [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] [[Barry McElduff]] was suspended from all party activity for three months after he posted a video online that relatives of the victims of the 1976 [[Kingsmill massacre]] described as callous and offensive. He resigned as an MP a week later.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0108/931701-barry-mcelduff-video/ Sinn F\u00e9in MP suspended for three months over Kingsmill video], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-08.</ref>\n* 12 January \u2013 [[Minister for Foreign Affairs (Ireland)|Minister for Foreign Affairs]] [[Simon Coveney]] met new [[Northern Ireland Secretary]] [[Karen Bradley]] for the first time. The two ministers discussed the re-establishment of power-sharing in the north.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0112/932689-karen-bradley/ Significant challenges over power-sharing - Coveney], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-12.</ref>\n* 14 January \u2013 The Citizens' Assembly recommended a ban on anonymous donations to political parties and campaign groups, weekend voting and lowering the voting age to 16.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0114/933172-assembly-voting-on-how-referendums-are-held/ Citizens' Assembly recommends raft of referendum changes], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-14.</ref>\n* 15 January \u2013 [[Garda\u00ed]] announced that they are to conduct a review into [[Kerry Babies|the death of a baby]] whose body was found on a beach at [[Cahersiveen]] in [[County Kerry]] 33 years ago.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/garda-to-begin-review-into-1984-kerry-babies-case-822881.html \"Garda to begin review into 1984 Kerry Babies case\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-01-15.</ref>\n* 16 January \u2013 Garda\u00ed apologised to Joanne Hayes for the stress and pain she was put through as part of the original investigation into the murder of 'Baby John' in Kerry in 1984.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/baby-john-deserves-the-truth-garda-in-public-appeal-as-apology-issued-to-joanne-hayes-over-kerry-babies-investigation-36494480.html \"'Baby John deserves the truth' - garda\u00ed in public appeal as apology issued to Joanne Hayes over Kerry Babies investigation\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-16.</ref>\n* 17 January \n** Taoiseach Leo Varadkar said that the [[European Union]] is at a decisive point in its future when he addressed [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]]s in the [[European Parliament]] in the first of a series of debates between EU government leaders and MEPs on the future of the EU.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/five-things-the-taoiseach-said-in-his-special-address-to-the-european-parliament-36498158.html Five things the Taoiseach said in his special address to the European Parliament], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-17.</ref>\n**Opening statements on the Report of the Joint Committee on the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|Eighth Amendment of the Constitution]] were made in the D\u00e1il, with [[Minister for Health (Ireland)|Minister for Health]] [[Simon Harris (politician)|Simon Harris]] describing the commencement of the debate as an historic one.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/oireachtas/harris-raises-kerry-babies-and-ann-lovett-cases-in-abortion-debate-1.3358750?mode=sample&auth-failed=1&pw-origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Foireachtas%2Fminister-references-kerry-babies-and-ann-lovett-cases-in-d%25C3%25A1il-abortion-debate-1.3358750 \"Harris raises Kerry babies and Ann Lovett cases in abortion debate\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-01-17.</ref>\n* 18 January \n** [[Minister for Transport (Ireland)|Minister for Transport]] [[Shane Ross]] accidentally voted against his own Road Traffic Bill in the D\u00e1il.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/blunder-sees-shane-ross-almost-vote-against-his-own-drinkdriving-crackdown-in-the-dil-36503578.html \"Blunder sees Shane Ross almost vote against his own drink-driving crackdown in the D\u00e1il\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-18.</ref>\n** [[Fianna F\u00e1il]] leader [[Miche\u00e1l Martin]] announces his support for the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|repeal of the Eighth Amendment]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0119/934439-eighth-amendment/|title=Eighth Amendment 'causes real damage to women' - Martin|publisher=RT\u00c9|date=18 January 2018|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n* 20 January \u2013 [[Mary Lou McDonald]] was confirmed as Sinn F\u00e9in's President-elect by [[Gerry Adams]] at a meeting of the party Ard Comhairle and its Northern region organisation in [[Belfast]]. She was he only candidate for the leadership.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/i-feel-an-enormous-sense-of-pride-mary-lou-mcdonald-is-the-sole-candidate-in-race-for-sinn-fin-party-president-36510443.html \"'I feel an enormous sense of pride' - Mary Lou McDonald is the sole candidate in race for Sinn F\u00e9in party president\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-20.</ref>\n* 25 January \u2013 The D\u00e1il passed legislation to allow the sale of alcohol on [[Good Friday]] for the first time in over 90 years.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pubs-to-open-on-good-friday-almost-100-years-after-ban-was-introduced-36530715.html \"Pubs to open on Good Friday almost 100 years after ban was introduced\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-25.</ref>\n* 27 January \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar announced that he will be campaigning for more liberal abortion laws in the forthcoming referendum on the repeal of the Eighth Amendment.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0127/936367-eighth-amendment/ \"Taoiseach to campaign to liberalise abortion laws\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-27.</ref>\n* 29 January \n**It was announced that [[Michelle O'Neill]] is to be the new deputy leader of Sinn F\u00e9in after it was confirmed she was the only candidate nominated for the post.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0129/936884-michelle-oneill/ \"Michelle O'Neill the only candidate for Sinn F\u00e9in deputy role\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-29.</ref>\n**The Cabinet gave formal approval to the holding of a referendum on the Eighth Amendment.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0129/936910-eighth-amendment-cabinet-referendum/ \"Cabinet agrees to hold referendum on Eighth Amendment\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-29.</ref>\n\n===February===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 3 February \u2013 Brexit supporter [[Nigel Farage]] said at a Dublin conference that there was \"a gap in the political market\" in Ireland for a party to push for an Irish exit from the European Union.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/nigel-farage-spots-gap-in-irish-political-market-for-irexit-party-1.3379310 \"Nigel Farage spots \u2018gap\u2019 in Irish political market for Irexit party\"],'' Irish Times'', 2018-02-03.</ref>\n* 5 February \u2013 More than 30 homes in 12 counties were searched as part of an investigation into the possession and distribution of child abuse images.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/crime/2018/0205/938458-operation-ketch/ 30 homes in 12 counties searched in operation over child abuse images], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-05.</ref>\n* 7 February \u2013 More than 30 secondary school students and two adults were taken to hospital after a school bus and a car collided in [[Caherconlish]], [[County Limerick]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/thirty-six-treated-in-hospital-after-school-bus-crash-in-limerick-1.3383211 \"Thirty-six treated in hospital after school bus crash in Limerick\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-02-07.</ref>\n* 9 February \u2013 The EU's chief Brexit negotiator [[Michel Barnier]] said the UK's decision to leave the EU single market and customs union will mean checks at the Irish border are \"unavoidable\".<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0209/939428-brexit-talks/ Davis highlights contradiction between EU and Barnier], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-09.</ref>\n* 10 February \u2013 Mary Lou McDonald was formally elected as President of Sinn F\u00e9in at a special [[Ard Fheis]] at the [[Royal Dublin Society|RDS]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/mary-lou-mcdonald-assumes-sinn-fin-leadership-insisting-the-war-is-long-over-36589125.html \"Mary Lou McDonald assumes Sinn F\u00e9in leadership insisting 'the war is long over'\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-02-10.</ref>\n* 12 February \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar and [[British Prime Minister]] [[Theresa May]] held talks at [[Stormont Estate|Stormont]] in an effort to resolve the deadlock in establishing the [[Northern Ireland Executive|Executive]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ulster/2018/0212/940012-stormont/ \"May says there is 'basis for an agreement' at Stormont\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-12.</ref>\n* 14 February \u2013 A three-year-old girl died following an alleged assault at her home in Dublin the previous Saturday.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0214/940609-shankill/ \"Girl, 3, dies following alleged assault in Dublin\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-14.</ref>\n* 16 February \u2013 The government launched a \u20ac116 billion development plan for the country. Project Ireland 2040 is aiming to spread economic development across the country which will see a population expansion of one million people over the lifetime of the plan.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0216/941116-govt-project-2040-plan/ \"More homes, schools, hospitals and transport links in Govt development plans\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-16.</ref>\n* 20 February \u2013 The proposed wording that would be inserted in the [[Constitution of Ireland|Constitution]] should people vote to repeal the Eighth Amendment has been agreed by the Cabinet.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0220/942002-eighth-amendment/ \"Cabinet agrees draft wording for Constitution should people vote for repeal\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-20.</ref>\n* 25 February \u2013 Aodh\u00e1n \u00d3 Conch\u00fair, a 14-year-old student at Pobalscoil Chorca Dhuibhne, died following a head injury sustained while playing in a football match in [[Dingle]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/boy-14-dies-following-collision-during-gaa-match-in-co-kerry-1.3404916 \"Boy (14) dies following collision during GAA match in Co Kerry\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-02-25.</ref>\n* 28 February \u2013 Met \u00c9ireann issued a red weather warning, its most severe alert, for all of Munster and Leinster as the [[2018 Great Britain and Ireland cold wave|Beast from the East]] weather event arrived.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/environment/beast-from-the-east-status-red-snow-alert-in-place-until-friday-1.3408511 \"Beast from the East: Status Red snow alert in place until Friday\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-02-28.</ref>\n\n===March===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 March \u2013 The Status Red snow and ice warning was extended to the entire country with blizzard conditions expected. Taoiseach Leo Varadkar called on people to heed public safety warnings about the blizzard conditions that are expected and to be safe at home by 4pm on Thursday.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0228/944081-weather-snow/ Status Red alert issued for all counties ahead of blizzard], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-01.</ref>\n* 2 March  \n**Two separate weather warnings were in place for the country tonight as blizzard-like conditions and exceptionally high accumulations of snow were expected with the arrival of [[Storm Emma]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0301/944315-storm-emma/ Blizzard-like conditions, heavy snow expected in parts of country], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-02.</ref>\n**Taoiseach Leo Varadkar ordered a general review of the Government's Strategic Communications Unit (SCU) after a week of controversy over advertorials for Project Ireland 2040.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/varadkar-orders-review-of-communications-unit-36660862.html Varadkar orders review of communications unit] Irish Independent, 2018-03-02.</ref>\n* 3 March \u2013 A vote in [[Lisdoonvarna]] returned a 93% rejection of plans by the Reception and Integration Agency (RIA) to house asylum seekers in the King Thomond Hotel.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/archives/2018/0303/ireland/lisdoonvarna-votes-93-against-asylum-seekers-467817.html \"Lisdoonvarna votes 93% against asylum seekers\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-03-03.</ref>\n* 4 March \u2013 A 27-year-old man appeared in court in [[Dundalk]] charged with the murder of Detective Garda Adrian Donohoe in [[County Louth]] just over five years earlier.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/archives/2018/0305/ireland/man-charged-with-murder-of-garda-adrian-donohoe-467882.html \"Man charged with murder of Garda Adrian Donohoe\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-03-04.</ref>\n* 5 March \u2013 Thousands of people were without electricity, while water rationing was imposed in some areas as the country recovered from the recent bad weather.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/archives/2018/0305/ireland/thousands-lack-power-or-water-after-storm-emma-467881.html \"Thousands lack power or water after Storm Emma\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-03-05.</ref>\n* 6 March \u2013 [[Ryanair]] chief executive [[Michael O'Leary (businessman)|Michael O'Leary]] becomes Ireland's latest billionaire, earning himself a place on [[Forbes]]'s annual billionaire ranking.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/business/economy/ryanair-s-michael-o-leary-joins-forbes-billionaire-list-1.3417345 \"Ryanair\u2019s Michael O\u2019Leary joins Forbes billionaire list\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-03-06.</ref>\n* 8 March \n**The Cabinet agreed to hold a referendum asking voters to repeal the Eighth Amendment and \"provision be made in law for the regulation of termination of pregnancy\".<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/cabinet-agrees-to-table-legislation-to-hold-an-abortion-referendum-1.3419605 \"Cabinet agrees to table legislation to hold an abortion referendum\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-03-08.</ref>\n**Former [[President of Ireland|President]] [[Mary McAleese]] criticised the [[Catholic Church]] as \"an empire of misogyny\".<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-43330026 Catholic Church 'an empire of misogyny' - Mary McAleese] BBC News, 2018-03-08.</ref>\n* 10 March \u2013 Tens of thousands of people marched through [[Dublin]] in one of the country's biggest ever [[anti-abortion]] demonstrations.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/huge-crowds-join-prolife-march-in-city-36691934.html \"Huge crowds join pro-life march in city\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-03-11.</ref>\n* 12 March \n**The Taoiseach, speaking at an event in [[Oklahoma]], thanked members of the [[Choctaw Nation]] for the generosity shown by their ancestors to Ireland during the [[Great Famine (Ireland)|Great Famine]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0312/946719-varadkar-brexit/ Taoiseach announces Choctaw scholarship programme], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-12.</ref>\n**There were 714 patients on trolleys or on wards awaiting admission to a hospital bed \u2013 the highest number ever recorded.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/number-of-patients-on-hospital-trolleys-hits-new-high-of-714-1.3423937 Number of patients on hospital trolleys hits new high of 714], ''Irish Times'', 2018-03-12.</ref>\n* 14 March \n**36 people were arrested following days of Garda activity in the [[County Kilkenny|Kilkenny]]-[[County Carlow|Carlow]] area aimed at preventing crime and disrupting criminal activity.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0314/947470-kilkenny-carlow-arrests/ 36 people arrested in Kilkenny and Carlow], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-14.</ref>\n**Taoiseach Leo Varadkar confirmed that an invitation to US President Donald Trump to visit Ireland extended by his predecessor [[Enda Kenny]] still stands.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/taoiseach-to-invite-trump-to-ireland-1.3427112 \"Taoiseach to invite Trump to Ireland\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-03-14.</ref>\n**Students occupying [[Trinity College Dublin]]'s dining hall in a protest over extra charges were denied access to toilets and water by security at the college, according to the students' union.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/trinity-denies-student-protesters-claim-that-they-have-been-locked-in-with-no-food-or-toilet-access-832558.html \"Trinity denies student protesters' claim that they have been locked in with no food or toilet access\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-03-14.</ref>\n* 15 March \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar met US President Donald Trump in the [[White House]] where Trump said he would like to visit Ireland soon.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/us/donald-trump-tells-taoiseach-he-plans-to-visit-ireland-1.3428430 \"Donald Trump tells Taoiseach he plans to visit Ireland\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-03-15.</ref> He later had to clarify that he had not interfered in the planning process four years previously when Trump had asked him to intervene to block the creation of a wind farm near Trump's Doonbeg golf resort.\n* 16 March \u2013 The Taoiseach met [[Vice President of the United States|US Vice President]] [[Mike Pence]] at his [[Number One Observatory Circle|official residence]]. In a break with protocol, the media were not in attendance, however, it is understood that the Taoiseach did raise the issue of gay rights.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/mike-pence-refuses-to-answer-questions-about-media-ban-or-marriage-equality-as-varadkar-attends-breakfast-meeting-36711958.html \"Mike Pence refuses to answer questions about media ban or marriage equality as Varadkar attends breakfast meeting\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-03-16.</ref>\n* 17 March \u2013 The [[Ireland national rugby union team|Irish rugby team]] beat [[England national rugby union team|England]] 24\u201315, winning the [[Grand Slam (rugby union)|Grand Slam]] in addition to the [[2018 Six Nations Championship]] secured a week earlier.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/rugby/2018/0317/948251-ireland-england-report/|title=Grand Slam glory as Ireland dominate England in Twickenham|publisher=RT\u00c9|date=18 March 2018|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n* 19 March \u2013 The European Union and Britain agreed that there must be a \"backstop\" solution to ensure that there is no hard border on the island of Ireland. A backstop agreement would fully align Northern Ireland with the rules of the EU in order to avoid a hard border.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0319/948513-coveney-brexit-brussels/ EU, UK agree there should be 'backstop' on Irish border], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-19.</ref>\n* 20 March \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar discussed Brexit with [[German Chancellor]] [[Angela Merkel]] in [[Berlin]] during his first visit to the German capital as Taoiseach.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0320/948674-varadkar_germany_visit/ Germany 'fully supports' Ireland on border issue - Merkel] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-20.</ref>\n* 21 March \n**[[Pope Francis]] confirmed that he will make the first papal trip to Ireland in nearly 40 years, visiting Dublin for two days in August.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-confirms-he-will-make-first-papal-visit-to-ireland-in-nearly-40-years-36727608.html \"Pope Francis confirms he will make first papal visit to Ireland in nearly 40 years\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-03-21.</ref>\n**The second stage of the bill to allow for a referendum on the Eighth Amendment passed by a large majority in the D\u00e1il by 110 votes to 32.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0321/949062-politics/ \"Second stage of Referendum bill passes by large majority in D\u00e1il\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-21.</ref>\n* 27 March \n**The Minister for Foreign Affairs, Simon Coveney, informed the Russian Ambassador to Ireland that the \"accreditation of a member of his staff with diplomatic status is to be terminated\".<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/uncalled-for-senseless-and-regrettable-russian-ambassador-criticises-decision-to-expel-diplomat-from-ireland-36748355.html 'Uncalled for, senseless and regrettable' - Russian ambassador criticises decision to expel diplomat from Ireland], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-03-27.</ref>\n**The Minister for Health, Simon Harris, announced that the Cabinet approved the \"general scheme\" of the legislation on abortion that would be brought forward if the referendum on the Eighth Amendment was passed.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0327/950308-draft_abortion_bill/ \"Cabinet approves 'general scheme' of legislation on abortion\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-27.</ref>\n* 28 March \n**[[Ulster Rugby|Ulster]] and [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]] rugby player [[Paddy Jackson]] was acquitted of rape and sexual assault, while his teammate [[Stuart Olding]] was acquitted of rape.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/courts/2018/0328/950639-belfast-rape-trial/ 2Jackson and Olding acquitted of rape charges2], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-28.</ref>\n**The government announced that the referendum on repealing the Eighth Amendment will take place on 25 May.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/abortion-referendum/the-date-has-been-set-for-a-referendum-on-the-eighth-amendment-36753441.html \"The date has been set for a referendum on the Eighth Amendment\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-03-28.</ref>\n**New figures revealed that there were 1,739 homeless families recorded in February.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0328/950712-homeless/ 1,739 homeless families recorded in February], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-28.</ref>\n* 29 March \u2013 The Save the 8th campaign was launched in Dublin. The group is campaigning for a \"No\" vote in May's referendum on the Eighth Amendment of the Constitution.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/eighth-amendment/2018/0329/950911-save8th-campaign-launch/ Save the 8th campaign launches in Dublin], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-29.</ref>\n* 30 March \n**Pubs opened on [[Good Friday]] for the first time in 91 years.<ref>[http://www.thejournal.ie/good-friday-pub-ban-3928176-Mar2018/ Good Friday: There'll be winners and losers as pubs open for the first time since 1927] The Journal, 2018-03-30.</ref>\n**The [[Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (Ireland)|Department of Foreign Affairs]] confirmed that an Irish diplomat has been instructed to leave Russia.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/world/2018/0330/951161-russia-diplomacy/ One Irish diplomat instructed to leave Russia], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-30.</ref>\n\n===April===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 April \n**The [[1916 Easter Rising]] was commemorated around the country, while a military ceremony took place in [[O'Connell Street]] in Dublin.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0401/951465-easter-rising/ Ceremonies held to mark 1916 Easter Rising] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-04-01.</ref>\n**[[Sinn F\u00e9in]] deputy leader [[Michelle O'Neill]] called for an [[United Ireland|Irish unity]] referendum within five years.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/sinn-f%C3%A9in-urges-unity-referendum-within-five-years-1.3447391 Sinn F\u00e9in urges unity referendum wi