 investigation into the possession and distribution of child abuse images.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/several-child-sex-dolls-seized-as-gardai-raid-31-homes-in-operation-targeting-paedophiles-37158205.html Several 'child sex dolls' seized as gardai raid 31 homes in operation targeting paedophiles] Irish Independent, 2018-07-26.</ref>\n**MMA fighter Conor McGregor was sentenced to five days community service and is to undergo an anger management programme as part of a plea deal.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/world/2018/0726/981118-conor-mcgregor/ Five days' community service, anger management programme for Conor McGregor] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-26.</ref>\n* 27 July \u2013 Irish Water confirmed that the countrywide hosepipe ban introduced earlier this month will remain in place until the end of August.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/latest-national-hosepipe-ban-in-place-until-end-of-august-858199.html \"Latest: National hosepipe ban in place until end of August\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-07-27.</ref>\n* 30 July \u2013 The Minister for Finance agreed to pay [[Aidan Flanagan]] - a Garda and former [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]] [[hurling]] captain - \u20ac1.16m for injuries he suffered when making an arrest.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/courts/2018/0730/982038-aidan-flanagan/ \"Garda and former Tipperary hurler receives \u20ac1.16m damages for back injury\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-30.</ref>\n* 31 July \u2013 A dispute over a \u20ac3.3m winning [[National Lottery (Ireland)|Lotto]] ticket was resolved when the Court of Appeal ruled that Mary Walsh must pay \u20ac560,000 to her stepson David Walsh plus his legal costs after finding her stepson was part owner of and entitled to a one-sixth share of the winning ticket.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/33m-lotto-dispute-between-woman-and-stepson-resolved-859094.html \"\u20ac3.3m lotto dispute between woman and stepson resolved\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-31.</ref>\n\n===August===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 August\n** Cork's [[English Market]], one of the oldest municipal markets of its kind in the world, celebrated its 230th birthday.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/munster/2018/0801/982503-english-market/ Cork's English Market celebrates 230th birthday], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-01.</ref>\n** Organisers of the Papal visit delayed issuing tickets over concerns about the number of people travelling to the event by car.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/issuing-of-papal-visit-tickets-delayed-over-concerns-about-number-of-people-travelling-by-car-37175211.html \"Issuing of Papal visit tickets delayed over concerns about number of people travelling by car\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-08-01.</ref>\n* 2 August \u2013 [[An Post]] stated that up to 161 post offices might close after they confirmed the same number of postmasters applied for the company's voluntary retirement package.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/an-post-confirms-161-post-offices-may-close-859699.html \"An Post confirms 161 post offices may close\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-08-02.</ref>\n* 3 August \u2013 A post-mortem examination was to take place following the death of a [[transgender]] woman living in the male wing of a Direct Provision Centre in Galway.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/transgender-woman-dies-in-mens-wing-of-direct-provision-centre-in-galway-859924.html \"Transgender woman dies in men's wing of Direct Provision centre in Galway\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-08-03.</ref>\n* 4 August \n** The family of an Irishman who disappeared in 1985 were told that [[DNA]] analysis confirmed a match with a body that has remained unidentified in [[Wales]] since then.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0804/983128-missing-dowley-wales/ Unidentified body buried in Wales found be missing Irish man], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-04.</ref>\n** A recent gorse fire on [[Bray Head]] in [[County Wicklow]] has revealed an \u00c9IRE sign which dates from the [[Second World War]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/leinster/2018/0804/983116-eire-sign-bray-head/ WWII \u00c9IRE sign found on Bray Head following gorse fire], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-04.</ref>\n* 5 August \u2013 CEO of [[Sport Ireland]] [[John Treacy]] said the [[Ireland women's national field hockey team|Ireland women's hockey players]] did not have to each pay a levy of \u20ac550 to represent Ireland at the [[2018 Women's Hockey World Cup|World Cup]], despite reports that they had to because of a shortfall in funding.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0805/983286-sport-ireland-hockey-levy/ Sport Ireland denies hockey team had to pay levy to play at World Cup], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-05.</ref>\n* 6 August \u2013 Thousands of people gathered in Dublin city centre to welcome home Ireland's women's hockey team following their success at the Hockey World Cup.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0806/983406-hockey-homecoming/ Dublin homecoming for Ireland's hockey heroes], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-06.</ref>\n* 8 August \u2013 The Policing Authority identified fundamental flaws in the reform process of An Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na, which it said were barriers to effective progress.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0808/983846-policing-authority-gardai/ 'Significant' flaws identified in reform process of An Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-08.</ref>\n* 9 August \u2013 [[Academy Awards|Oscar]]-winning screenwriter and director [[Neil Jordan]] donated his archive to the [[National Library of Ireland]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/neil-jordan-donates-vast-archive-to-national-library-of-ireland-1.3590879 Neil Jordan donates \u2018vast\u2019 archive to National Library of Ireland], Irish Times, 2018-08-09.</ref>\n* 10 August \u2013 The HSE confirmed that the number of measles cases in an outbreak in Dublin had risen to 11.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/measles-outbreak-in-dublin-up-to-11-confirmed-cases-861214.html Measles outbreak in Dublin up to 11 confirmed cases], Irish Examiner, 2018-08-10.</ref>\n* 15 August \n** A ceremony was held in [[Omagh]] to remember the 29 people who were killed and the hundreds injured by a [[Real IRA]] [[Omagh bombing|bomb on this day 20 years ago]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/omagh-bombing-higgins-urges-vigilance-on-belfast-agreement-1.3596376 Omagh bombing: Higgins urges vigilance on Belfast Agreement], Irish Times, 2018-08-15.</ref>\n** More than 57,000 students received the results of their Leaving Certificate exams at their schools.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/education/2018/0815/985188-leaving-cert-exams/ Over 57,000 students receive Leaving Certificate results], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-15.</ref>\n* 16 August \u2013 [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Boston|Archbishop of Boston]], [[Se\u00e1n Patrick O'Malley]], withdrew from the [[World Meeting of Families]] where he was to chair a debate on child safeguarding.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/prominent-cardinal-cancels-attendance-at-world-meeting-of-families-37220919.html Prominent Cardinal cancels attendance at World Meeting of Families], Irish Independent, 2018-08-16.</ref>\n* 17 August \u2013 A new all-time high for private residential rents was reached for the ninth quarter in a row, according to a report from the property website Daft.ie.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/business/personal-finance/property-mortgages/rents-hits-recordhigh-as-its-now-274-more-per-month-than-celtic-tiger-peak-37225104.html Rents hits record-high as it's now \u20ac274 more per month than Celtic Tiger peak], Irish Independent, 2018-08-17.</ref>\n* 18 August  \n** [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Washington|Archbishop of Washington]], [[Donald Wuerl]], withdrew from the World Meeting of Families due to controversies about his role in cover-ups of clerical child sexual abuse.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/the-pope-in-ireland/2018/0818/985952-wuerl-ireland/ Cardinal Wuerl withdraws from Dublin meeting], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-18.</ref>\n** Taoiseach Leo Varadkar said he wants Fianna F\u00e1il to commit to a two-year extension of the [[confidence and supply]] deal, and agree to holding a [[Next Irish general election|General Election in 2020]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0818/985964-varadkar-fianna-fail-drogheda/ Varadkar wants Fianna F\u00e1il to extend confidence and supply deal], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-18.</ref>\n* 19 August \u2013 Journalist [[Gemma O'Doherty]] announced her intention to run for the presidency.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/journalist-gemma-o-doherty-announces-intention-to-run-for-the-presidency-1.3601337 Journalist Gemma O\u2019Doherty announces intention to run for the presidency], Irish Times, 2018-08-19.</ref>\n* 20 August \u2013 [[Iarnr\u00f3d \u00c9ireann]] announced the development of a new railway station on the [[Dublin Suburban Rail#Western Commuter|Maynooth commuter line]] at Pelletstown in [[West Dublin]].<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/planning-awarded-for-new-train-station-at-pelletstown-for-dublin-commuters-863283.html Planning awarded for new train station at Pelletstown for Dublin commuters], Irish Examiner, 2018-08-21.</ref>\n* 21 August \u2013 A woman in her 50s was arrested after she attempted to drive a [[Nissan Micra]] through the gates of [[Government Buildings]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/breaking-news/irish-news/woman-arrested-after-car-crashes-into-government-buildings-37237368.html Woman arrested after car crashes into Government Buildings], Irish Independent, 2018-08-21.</ref>\n* 25 August \n** [[Pope Francis]] began a 2-day [[Pope Francis's visit to Ireland|visit to Ireland]]. It was only the second papal visit to Ireland ever and the first since [[Pope John Paul II]] in 1979.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/it-touches-my-heart-pope-francis-on-returning-to-ireland-as-he-arrives-in-dublin-airport-37250561.html 'It touches my heart' - Pope Francis on returning to Ireland as he arrives in Dublin Airport], Irish Independent, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** In his first official engagement, the Pope held private discussions in [[Spanish language|Spanish]] with President Higgins on issues including climate change, inequality, poverty and migration.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/with-gratitude-for-the-warm-welcome-may-god-guide-you-37252231.html 'With gratitude for the warm welcome... may God guide you'], Irish Independent, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** In a speech in front of the Pope at [[Dublin Castle]], the Taoiseach said that the history of the Catholic Church in Ireland was one of \"sorrow and of shame.\"<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/welcome-to-a-new-ireland-varadkar-calls-for-action-after-words-of-condemnation-37252190.html Welcome to a new Ireland - Varadkar calls for \u2018action\u2019 after words of condemnation], Irish Independent, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** At [[St. Mary's Pro-Cathedral]], the Pope said a silent prayer at the Candle of Innocence to remember the survivors of clerical and institutional abuse.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/pope-francis-in-ireland/2018/0825/987433-pope-francis-address/  Pope tells survivors those who cover-up abuse are 'filth'], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** After a journey through the streets of Dublin, the Pope visited the Capuchin Day Centre for Homeless People.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/pope-francis-in-ireland/2018/0825/987499-pope-homeless-tribute/ Pope pays tribute to dignity of homeless at day centre], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** During a 90-minute meeting with eight Irish survivors of clerical, religious and institutional abuse, the Pope described those who covered up the abuse as \"[[Wikt:caca#Spanish|caca]]\".<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/survivors-stunned-by-caca-verdict-on-coverup-37255014.html Survivors stunned by 'caca' verdict on cover-up], Irish Independent, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n** The Pope ended his first day in Ireland by attending the [[World Meeting of Families]] concert at [[Croke Park]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/pope-francis-warns-families-of-threat-posed-by-social-media-at-uplifting-croke-park-concert-37251616.html Pope Francis warns families of 'threat' posed by social media at uplifting Croke Park concert], Irish Independent, 2018-08-25.</ref>\n* 25 August  \n** On the second day of his visit to Ireland, the Pope began by visiting [[Knock Shrine]] in [[County Mayo]] where he spoke about the \"open wound\" of clerical child sexual abuse.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/pope-francis-lauded-at-knock-for-raising-open-wound-of-sex-abuse-1.3608239 Pope Francis lauded at Knock for raising \u2018open wound\u2019 of sex abuse], Irish Times, 2018-08-26.</ref>\n** 1,000 people held a silent vigil in [[Tuam]] to remember the Tuam Babies, while thousands attended the Stand4Truth event in Dublin to show solidarity with victims of abuse.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0826/987636-pope-protest/ Thousands attend Tuam vigil and Dublin rally to coincide with Papal mass], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-26.</ref>\n** The Pope celebrated Mass at the [[Phoenix Park]], however, according to an official statistic supplied by the [[Office of Public Works]], fewer than 152,000 people attended, far short of the expected 500,000.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/crowds-for-phoenix-park-mass-fall-well-below-expected-level-of-500000-37254339.html Crowds for Phoenix Park Mass fall well below expected level of 500,000], Irish Independent, 2018-08-26.</ref><ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pope-francis-in-ireland/revealed-finally-how-many-people-attended-papal-mass-in-phoenix-park-37335645.html Revealed (finally): How many people attended papal Mass in Phoenix Park] Irish Independent, 2018-09-20.</ref>\n* 28 August \n** It was announced that more than 150 post offices around the country are to close as part of a deal reached between An Post and the Irish Postmasters' Union.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/an-post-publishes-locations-of-159-post-offices-set-to-close-1.3610543 An Post publishes locations of 159 post offices set to close], Irish Times, 2018-08-28.</ref>\n** [[Minister for Housing, Planning and Local Government]] [[Eoghan Murphy]] confirmed that the Presidential Election will be held on Friday 26 October.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/order-allowing-presidential-election-likely-to-be-signed-today-864979.html Latest: Presidential election to take place in October], Irish Examiner, 2018-08-28.</ref>\n* 29 August \u2013 Businessman [[Se\u00e1n Gallagher]] announced that he is going to seek a nomination to run for the presidency for a second time.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/businessman-sean-gallagher-launches-second-bid-to-become-president-of-ireland-37263034.html Businessman Sean Gallagher launches second bid to become President of Ireland], Irish Independent, 2018-08-29.</ref>\n* 30 August  \n** [[Virgin Media Television (Republic of Ireland)|Virgin Media Television]] was officially launched, with new channel names and identities going live and replacing the old [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]] stations.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2018/0830/988491-virgin-media-television-is-officially-launched/ Virgin Media Television launched], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-30.</ref>\n** Businessman [[Peter Casey]] announced that he is seeking a nomination to contest the Presidential Election.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/dragons-den-star-peter-casey-seeking-presidential-nomination-865542.html Election candidates refusing salary 'demeans the office of President', says Justice Minister], Irish Examiner, 2018-08-30.</ref>\n* 31 August \u2013 The American [[White House]] published a statement that [[Donald Trump]] would visit Ireland on 11 November. President Trump would visit France on the 11th as part of the [[Armistice Day|commemoration of the 100th anniversary]] of the [[Armistice of 11 November 1918|World War I armistice]], and the Irish Government issued a statement that the Irish visit will probably follow this. Various political parties announced their intention to protest against the visit, while the [[Minister for Foreign Affairs and Trade|Minister for Foreign Affairs]] stated that facilitation of the visit was not an Irish endorsement of Trump's politics. The White House cancelled the visit on 11 September (q.v.).<ref>[https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/statement-press-secretary-31/ Statement from the Press Secretary] The White House, 2018-08-31.</ref><ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0831/990843-trump-to-visit-ireland-in-november-white-house-says/ Trump to visit Ireland in November, White House says] RT\u00c9, 2018-09-01.</ref><ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0901/990922-donald-trump-ireland-visit/ Call for protests during Donald Trump's visit to Ireland] RT\u00c9, 2018-09-01.</ref>\n\n===September===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 3 September \n** [[Drew Harris]] was sworn in as Garda Commissioner at a ceremony at Kevin Street Garda Station in the early hours of the morning.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0903/991217-drew-harris-sworn-in/  Garda Commissioner and Justice Minister discuss garda reform], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-03.</ref>\n** [[Gavin Duffy]] and [[Joan Freeman (politician)|Joan Freeman]] received endorsements from two separate county councils for nominations to run as candidates in the Presidential Election.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0903/991245-presidential-candidates-kerry-cork/ Joan Freeman secures Cork City Council presidential endorsement], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-03.</ref>\n* 6 September\n** The inquest into the death of [[Dolores O'Riordan]] found that the singer-songwriter died by drowning due to alcohol intoxication.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/were-just-glad-it-is-over-family-of-dolores-oriordan-as-coroner-records-her-death-as-accidental-37289371.html 'We're just glad it is over' - Family of Dolores O'Riordan as coroner records her death as 'accidental'], Irish Independent, 2018-08-06.</ref>\n** Searches were carried out in at least five counties in the east of the country by Garda\u00ed investigating a multimillion-euro fraud network.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/crime/2018/0906/991961-crime-raids/  Searches carried out in five counties in fraud crack down], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-08-06.</ref>\n* 10 September \u2013 Sean Gallagher and Joan Freeman secured nominations to contest the Presidential Election after receiving the support of four separate local authorities.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0910/992732-presidential-election-councils/  Freeman and Gallagher both secure nominations for \u00c1ras bids], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-10.</ref>\n* 11 September \n** Minister for Health Simon Harris said he still plans to set up a Commission of Investigation into the CervicalCheck crisis, despite the author of the review into the controversy saying he did not think one was needed.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0911/992972-scally-cervical-check/ Harris still plans to have CervicalCheck commission], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-11.</ref>\n** [[Donald Trump]] cancelled his visit to Ireland, planned for November, which he announced just 11 days ago. Both the announcement of the visit and its cancellation took the Irish government by considerable surprise.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0911/993113-donald-trump-ireland-visit/ Trump visit to Ireland in November will not go ahead] RT\u00c9, 2018-09-11.</ref>\n** Six people were arrested on North Frederick Street in Dublin in connection with the occupation of a house by a group of activists protesting over the housing crisis.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/dublin/2018/0911/993167-north-frederick-street/ Six arrested during protest in Dublin city centre], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-11.</ref>\n* 12 September \n** The Scally Report confirmed there was \"a deficit of clear governance and reporting lines\" between CervicalCheck, the National Screening Service and HSE management.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/cervical-screening-system-was-doomed-to-fail-at-some-point-scally-report-finds-1.3626738 Cervical screening system was doomed to fail at some point, Scally report finds], Irish Times, 2018-09-12.</ref>\n** 1,000 protesters demonstrating over the eviction of people from a repossessed building blocked the junction between Dublin's Parnell Street and O'Connell Street.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/dublin/2018/0912/993266-dublin-protest/  Housing protesters hold demonstration on O'Connell St], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-12.</ref>\n** The Cabinet approved the nomination of [[Edward F. Crawford (businessman)|Edward F. Crawford]] as the new US ambassador to Ireland.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0912/993250-ambassador/ Cabinet approves Edward F Crawford as US ambassador to Ireland], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-09-12.</ref>\n* 13 September \u2013 [[Mary Lou McDonald]] apologised to alleged sex abuse victim [[M\u00e1ir\u00eda Cahill]] after a report found her case was failed by a disjointed police investigation.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-45503335M\u00e1ir\u00eda Cahill: PSNI failed women over IRA sex abuse claims], BBC News, 2018-09-13.</ref>\n* 14 September \u2013 Businessman Gavin Duffy secured a nomination to contest the Presidential Election after receiving the support of four local authorities.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0914/993739-presidential-election/ Duffy secures four nominations to enter \u00c1r