ft)]]\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 2 November \u2013 [[Leonard Enright]], 65, hurler ([[Patrickswell GAA|Patrickswell]], [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]]), cancer.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/hurling/limerick-legend-and-threetime-all-star-leonard-enright-passes-away-37487977.html Limerick legend and three-time All Star Leonard Enright passes away], independent.ie</ref>\n* 3 November \u2013 Noel Hanlon, 78, businessman, cancer.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/business/irish/he-will-be-remembered-as-a-visionary-businessman-irish-entrepreneur-noel-hanlon-dies-37490119.html 'He will be remembered as a visionary businessman' - Irish entrepreneur Noel Hanlon dies], independent.ie</ref>\n* 6 November \u2013 [[Cliffs of Moher (horse)|Cliffs of Moher]], 4, thoroughbred racehorse, euthanised.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/horse-racing/aidan-obriens-cliffsofmoher-put-down-as-melbourne-cup-sees-firstever-british-win-37496962.html Aidan O'Brien's Cliffsofmoher put down as Melbourne Cup sees first-ever British win], independent.ie</ref>\n* 7 November \u2013 [[M\u00edche\u00e1l \u00d3 S\u00failleabh\u00e1in]], 67, musician, composer and academic.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/music-news/leading-irish-musician-and-composer-mchel-silleabhin-dies-aged-67-37504980.html Leading Irish musician and composer M\u00edche\u00e1l \u00d3 S\u00failleabh\u00e1in dies aged 67], independent.ie</ref>\n* 8 November \u2013 Virginia Cole, 71, actress, cancer.<ref>https://irishequity.ie/tribute-to-actress-virginia-cole/</ref>\n* 10 November \u2013 Paddy Clarke, Gaelic football [[Manager (Gaelic Games)|manager]] ([[Louth GAA|Louth]], [[Ireland international rules football team|Ireland]]).<ref>[https://www.dundalkdemocrat.ie/news/national-sport/347100/rip-former-louth-manager-paddy-clarke-passes-away.html RIP | Former Louth manager Paddy Clarke passes away], dundalkdemocrat.ie</ref>\n* 13 November\n** Paul McKeever, 39, Gaelic football referee ([[Antrim GAA|Antrim]]), illness.<ref>[http://hoganstand.com/Article/Index/292592 Sad passing of Antrim referee Paul McKeever], hoganstand.com</ref>\n** James Mortell, army officer and first person to be seen on [[RT\u00c9|Telef\u00eds \u00c9ireann]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/1117/1011582-james-mortell-death/ Funeral held for first person seen on Irish television in 1961], rte.ie</ref>\n* 15 November \u2013 [[Sonny Knowles]], 86, singer.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/music/music-news/tributes-pour-in-for-dublin-singer-sonny-knowles-who-has-died-aged-86-37532210.html Tributes pour in for Dublin singer Sonny Knowles who has died aged 86], independent.ie</ref>\n* 16 November \u2013 [[Alec Finn]], 74, English-born trad musician ([[De Dannan]]).<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/president-leads-tributes-after-death-of-de-danann-s-alec-finn-1.3700174 President leads tributes after death of De Danann\u2019s Alec Finn], irishtimes.com</ref>\n* 18 November \u2013 [[Weeshie Fogarty]], 77, Gaelic footballer ([[Killarney Legion]], [[Kerry GAA|Kerry]]), referee and sports broadcaster ([[Radio Kerry]]).<ref>[https://www.balls.ie/gaa/weeshie-fogarty-rip-401089 Legendary Kerry Broadcaster Weeshie Fogarty Dies Aged 77]</ref>\n* 19 November \u2013 Nan Ghriallais, [[Sean-n\u00f3s song|sean-n\u00f3s]] singer, long illness.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/nuacht/2018/1120/1012204-an-t-amhranai-sean-nois-mor-le-ra-nan-ghriallais-tar-eis-bhais/ An t-amhr\u00e1na\u00ed sean-n\u00f3is m\u00f3r le r\u00e1 Nan Ghriallais tar \u00e9is bh\u00e1is]</ref>\n* 20 November \u2013 Sandy Harsch, 76, radio presenter, short illness.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/culture/2018/1120/1012187-rte-radio-1-presenter-sandy-harsch-dies-aged-76/ RT\u00c9 Radio 1 presenter Sandy Harsch dies aged 76]</ref>\n* 22 November \u2013 Tom Considine, former Secretary-General of the [[Department of Finance (Ireland)|Department of Finance]], short illness.<ref>[https://www.limerickleader.ie/news/home/349802/tributes-paid-to-hugely-respectedmember-ofuniversity-of-limerick-governing-authority.html Tributes paid to \u2018hugely respected\u2019 member of University of Limerick Governing Authority]</ref>\n* 26 November \u2013 [[Sinndar]], 21, racehorse.<ref>[https://www.paulickreport.com/news/bloodstock/european-champion-sinndar-dies-at-age-21/ European Champion Sinndar Dies At Age 21]</ref> (death announced on this date)\n\n===December===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n[[File:garlands.jpg|thumb|120px|upright|right|[[Se\u00e1n Garland]]]]\n* 6 December \n** [[D\u00f3nall Farmer]], 81, actor (''[[Glenroe]]''), film director and producer.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2018/1206/1015498-glenroe-star-donall-farmer-has-died/ | title=Glenroe star D\u00f3nall Farmer has died | publisher=RT\u00c9 | date=6 December 2018}}</ref>\n** [[Jerome O'Shea]], 87, Gaelic footballer ([[South Kerry GAA|South Kerry]], [[Kerry GAA|Kerry]], [[Munster GAA|Munster]]), short illness.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/three-time-kerry-all-ireland-winner-jerome-oshea-dies-aged-87-890440.html Three time Kerry All-Ireland winner Jerome O'Shea dies aged 87]</ref>\n** Peter O'Reilly, 78, fly fisherman and author.<ref>[https://www.pressreader.com/ireland/sunday-independent-ireland/20181216/282235191755951 Obituary: Peter O'Reilly]</ref>\n* 13 December \u2013 [[Se\u00e1n Garland]], 84, politician, General Secretary of the [[Workers' Party of Ireland]] (1977\u20131990).<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/1213/1017096-sean-garland-death/ Former Workers' Party president Se\u00e1n Garland dies aged 84]</ref>\n* 23 December \u2013 [[Eileen Battersby]], 60, American-born literary critic and author (''[[Irish Times]]''), traffic collision.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/1224/1018911-eileen-battersby/ Literary critic Eileen Battersby dies following car crash]</ref>\n* 26 December \u2013 Jer O'Leary, 70s, actor (''[[Michael Collins (film)|Michael Collins]]'', ''[[In the Name of the Father (film)|In the Name of the Father]]'').<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/actor-jer-o-leary-best-known-for-big-jim-larkin-role-dies-1.3741862 Actor Jer O\u2019Leary, best known for \u2018Big Jim Larkin\u2019 role, dies]</ref>\n* 29 December \u2013 [[Scott Doran]], 44, Gaelic footballer ([[Wexford GAA|Wexford]], [[London GAA|London]]).<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/gaelic-football/tributes-paid-to-former-wexford-footballer-scott-doran-who-passes-away-aged-44-37667222.html Tributes paid to former Wexford footballer Scott Doran who passes away aged 44]</ref>\n* 31 December \u2013 [[Mark Killilea Jnr]], 79, politician.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/former-fianna-fil-mep-and-minister-dies-37671972.html Former Fianna F\u00e1il MEP and minister dies]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Years in Ireland}}\n{{Europe topic|2018 in}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|Northern Ireland|2018 in Northern Ireland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{YearInIrelandNav|2018}}\n\nEvents during the year '''2018 in Ireland'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n[[File:Michael D. Higgins 2006.jpg|thumb|120px|upright|right|[[President of Ireland|President]] [[Michael D. Higgins]]]]\n* [[President of Ireland|President]]: [[Michael D. Higgins]] \n* [[Taoiseach]]: [[Leo Varadkar]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[T\u00e1naiste]]: [[Simon Coveney]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[Minister for Finance (Ireland)|Minister for Finance]]: [[Paschal Donohoe]] ([[Fine Gael|FG]])\n* [[Chief Justice of Ireland|Chief Justice]]: [[Frank Clarke (judge)|Frank Clarke]] \n* [[D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann|D\u00e1il]]: [[Members of the 32nd D\u00e1il|32nd]]\n* [[Seanad \u00c9ireann|Seanad]]: [[Members of the 25th Seanad|25th]]\n\n== Events ==\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n<!-- NOTE: Do not add national holidays (e.g Christmas, Easter) or anything that occurs every year (e.g Clocks go back) from this section -->\n\n=== January ===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 January \n**[[Teachta D\u00e1la|TDs]] rang in the [[2018|new year]] with a pay increase of \u20ac3,600, with a further increase to follow in October, bringing the total increase in 2018 to \u20ac4,500, yielding an annual salary of \u20ac94,500.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/happy-new-year-for-tds-who-wake-up-to-a-3600-pay-hike-36448456.html \"Happy new year for TDs - who wake up to a \u20ac3,600 pay hike\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-01.</ref>\n** The [[Road Safety Authority]] (RSA), published provisional statistics for 2017, which showed a 15% drop in road deaths compared with the previous year. A total of 158 people lost their lives on Ireland's roads compared to 186 lives lost in 2016. It represented 28 fewer fatalities on the previous year and was the lowest figure for annual road deaths since they were first officially recorded in 1959.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/breaking-news/irish-news/road-deaths-at-lowest-level-on-record-in-2017-36449405.html \"Road deaths at lowest level on record in 2017\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-02.</ref>\n* 2 January\n**A record 656 patients were on trolleys or on wards waiting for admission to a bed, according to the [[Irish Nurses and Midwives Organisation]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0102/930611-hospital-trolleys/ \"Record 656 patients waiting for hospital bed\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-02.</ref>\n**[[Met \u00c9ireann]] issued two Status Orange warnings as [[Storm Eleanor]] swept across the country bringing gusts of up to 130&nbsp;km/h and flooding in some areas. Up to 55,000 [[Electricity Supply Board|ESB]] customers in the west and north west of the country were left without power.<ref>[https://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/storm-eleanor-55000-esb-customers-without-power-amid-flooding-and-high-winds-821010.html Storm Eleanor: 55,000 ESB customers without power amid flooding and high winds], breakingnews.ie, 2018-01-02.</ref>\n* 3 January \u2013 The level of hospital overcrowding increased to a national record of 677 patients, according to the latest figures from the Irish Nurses and Midwives Organisation.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0103/930787-trolleys/ \"Hospital overcrowding increases to record level of 677 patients\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-03.</ref>\n* 4 January \u2013 [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]] apologised to patients who have experienced long delays and waits on trolleys in emergency departments as the [[Health Service Executive]] revealed that there were 12 children on trolleys in the three children's hospitals in [[Dublin]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/health/2018/0104/930977-hospital-overcrowding/  Taoiseach apologises to patients over emergency department delays], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-05.</ref>\n* 6 January \u2013 The [[diocese of Down and Connor]] suspended the [[Kiss of peace|sign of peace]] between people at mass in response to the surge in cases of influenza.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/religion-and-beliefs/diocese-bans-the-sign-of-peace-amid-australian-flu-fears-1.3347299 \"Diocese bans the \u2018sign of peace\u2019 amid Australian flu fears\"], ''[[The Irish Times]]'' (Dublin), 2018-01-06.</ref>\n* 7 January \u2013 Met \u00c9ireann issued a Status Orange low temperature warning for many counties, with temperatures plummeting to as low as -6C over night.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0107/931577-weather-warning/ Orange weather warning in place as temperatures plummet], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-07.</ref>\n* 8 January \u2013 [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] [[Barry McElduff]] was suspended from all party activity for three months after he posted a video online that relatives of the victims of the 1976 [[Kingsmill massacre]] described as callous and offensive. He resigned as an MP a week later.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0108/931701-barry-mcelduff-video/ Sinn F\u00e9in MP suspended for three months over Kingsmill video], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-08.</ref>\n* 12 January \u2013 [[Minister for Foreign Affairs (Ireland)|Minister for Foreign Affairs]] [[Simon Coveney]] met new [[Northern Ireland Secretary]] [[Karen Bradley]] for the first time. The two ministers discussed the re-establishment of power-sharing in the north.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0112/932689-karen-bradley/ Significant challenges over power-sharing - Coveney], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-12.</ref>\n* 14 January \u2013 The Citizens' Assembly recommended a ban on anonymous donations to political parties and campaign groups, weekend voting and lowering the voting age to 16.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0114/933172-assembly-voting-on-how-referendums-are-held/ Citizens' Assembly recommends raft of referendum changes], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-14.</ref>\n* 15 January \u2013 [[Garda\u00ed]] announced that they are to conduct a review into [[Kerry Babies|the death of a baby]] whose body was found on a beach at [[Cahersiveen]] in [[County Kerry]] 33 years ago.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/garda-to-begin-review-into-1984-kerry-babies-case-822881.html \"Garda to begin review into 1984 Kerry Babies case\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-01-15.</ref>\n* 16 January \u2013 Garda\u00ed apologised to Joanne Hayes for the stress and pain she was put through as part of the original investigation into the murder of 'Baby John' in Kerry in 1984.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/baby-john-deserves-the-truth-garda-in-public-appeal-as-apology-issued-to-joanne-hayes-over-kerry-babies-investigation-36494480.html \"'Baby John deserves the truth' - garda\u00ed in public appeal as apology issued to Joanne Hayes over Kerry Babies investigation\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-16.</ref>\n* 17 January \n** Taoiseach Leo Varadkar said that the [[European Union]] is at a decisive point in its future when he addressed [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]]s in the [[European Parliament]] in the first of a series of debates between EU government leaders and MEPs on the future of the EU.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/five-things-the-taoiseach-said-in-his-special-address-to-the-european-parliament-36498158.html Five things the Taoiseach said in his special address to the European Parliament], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-17.</ref>\n**Opening statements on the Report of the Joint Committee on the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|Eighth Amendment of the Constitution]] were made in the D\u00e1il, with [[Minister for Health (Ireland)|Minister for Health]] [[Simon Harris (politician)|Simon Harris]] describing the commencement of the debate as an historic one.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/oireachtas/harris-raises-kerry-babies-and-ann-lovett-cases-in-abortion-debate-1.3358750?mode=sample&auth-failed=1&pw-origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Foireachtas%2Fminister-references-kerry-babies-and-ann-lovett-cases-in-d%25C3%25A1il-abortion-debate-1.3358750 \"Harris raises Kerry babies and Ann Lovett cases in abortion debate\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-01-17.</ref>\n* 18 January \n** [[Minister for Transport (Ireland)|Minister for Transport]] [[Shane Ross]] accidentally voted against his own Road Traffic Bill in the D\u00e1il.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/blunder-sees-shane-ross-almost-vote-against-his-own-drinkdriving-crackdown-in-the-dil-36503578.html \"Blunder sees Shane Ross almost vote against his own drink-driving crackdown in the D\u00e1il\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-18.</ref>\n** [[Fianna F\u00e1il]] leader [[Miche\u00e1l Martin]] announces his support for the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|repeal of the Eighth Amendment]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0119/934439-eighth-amendment/|title=Eighth Amendment 'causes real damage to women' - Martin|publisher=RT\u00c9|date=18 January 2018|accessdate=19 January 2018}}</ref>\n* 20 January \u2013 [[Mary Lou McDonald]] was confirmed as Sinn F\u00e9in's President-elect by [[Gerry Adams]] at a meeting of the party Ard Comhairle and its Northern region organisation in [[Belfast]]. She was he only candidate for the leadership.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/i-feel-an-enormous-sense-of-pride-mary-lou-mcdonald-is-the-sole-candidate-in-race-for-sinn-fin-party-president-36510443.html \"'I feel an enormous sense of pride' - Mary Lou McDonald is the sole candidate in race for Sinn F\u00e9in party president\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-20.</ref>\n* 25 January \u2013 The D\u00e1il passed legislation to allow the sale of alcohol on [[Good Friday]] for the first time in over 90 years.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/pubs-to-open-on-good-friday-almost-100-years-after-ban-was-introduced-36530715.html \"Pubs to open on Good Friday almost 100 years after ban was introduced\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-01-25.</ref>\n* 27 January \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar announced that he will be campaigning for more liberal abortion laws in the forthcoming referendum on the repeal of the Eighth Amendment.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0127/936367-eighth-amendment/ \"Taoiseach to campaign to liberalise abortion laws\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-27.</ref>\n* 29 January \n**It was announced that [[Michelle O'Neill]] is to be the new deputy leader of Sinn F\u00e9in after it was confirmed she was the only candidate nominated for the post.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0129/936884-michelle-oneill/ \"Michelle O'Neill the only candidate for Sinn F\u00e9in deputy role\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-29.</ref>\n**The Cabinet gave formal approval to the holding of a referendum on the Eighth Amendment.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0129/936910-eighth-amendment-cabinet-referendum/ \"Cabinet agrees to hold referendum on Eighth Amendment\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-01-29.</ref>\n\n===February===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 3 February \u2013 Brexit supporter [[Nigel Farage]] said at a Dublin conference that there was \"a gap in the political market\" in Ireland for a party to push for an Irish exit from the European Union.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/nigel-farage-spots-gap-in-irish-political-market-for-irexit-party-1.3379310 \"Nigel Farage spots \u2018gap\u2019 in Irish political market for Irexit party\"],'' Irish Times'', 2018-02-03.</ref>\n* 5 February \u2013 More than 30 homes in 12 counties were searched as part of an investigation into the possession and distribution of child abuse images.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/crime/2018/0205/938458-operation-ketch/ 30 homes in 12 counties searched in operation over child abuse images], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-05.</ref>\n* 7 February \u2013 More than 30 secondary school students and two adults were taken to hospital after a school bus and a car collided in [[Caherconlish]], [[County Limerick]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/thirty-six-treated-in-hospital-after-school-bus-crash-in-limerick-1.3383211 \"Thirty-six treated in hospital after school bus crash in Limerick\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-02-07.</ref>\n* 9 February \u2013 The EU's chief Brexit negotiator [[Michel Barnier]] said the UK's decision to leave the EU single market and customs union will mean checks at the Irish border are \"unavoidable\".<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0209/939428-brexit-talks/ Davis highlights contradiction between EU and Barnier], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-02-09.</ref>\n* 10 February \u2013 Mary Lou McDonald was formally elected as President of Sinn F\u00e9in at a special [[Ard Fheis]] at the [[Royal Dublin Society|RDS]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/mary-lou-mcdonald-assumes-sinn-fin-leadership-insisting-the-war-is-long-over-36589125.html \"Mary Lou McDonald assumes 