-30.</ref>\n**The [[Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (Ireland)|Department of Foreign Affairs]] confirmed that an Irish diplomat has been instructed to leave Russia.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/world/2018/0330/951161-russia-diplomacy/ One Irish diplomat instructed to leave Russia], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-03-30.</ref>\n\n===April===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 April \n**The [[1916 Easter Rising]] was commemorated around the country, while a military ceremony took place in [[O'Connell Street]] in Dublin.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0401/951465-easter-rising/ Ceremonies held to mark 1916 Easter Rising] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-04-01.</ref>\n**[[Sinn F\u00e9in]] deputy leader [[Michelle O'Neill]] called for an [[United Ireland|Irish unity]] referendum within five years.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/sinn-f%C3%A9in-urges-unity-referendum-within-five-years-1.3447391 Sinn F\u00e9in urges unity referendum within five years], ''Irish Times'', 2018-04-01.</ref>\n* 3 April \u2013 Heavy overnight rain forced an early end to the Easter festival at [[Fairyhouse Racecourse]] due to a waterlogged track.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/sport/racing/2018/0403/951765-fairyhouse-cancelled-due-to-heavy-rainfall/ \"Fairyhouse card cancelled due to heavy rainfall\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-04-03.</ref>\n* 4 April \u2013 President Higgins signed a warrant granting a posthumous pardon to Myles Joyce who was wrongfully convicted and hanged over the murder of five people in 1882.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0404/952165-mam-trasna/ \"Pardon granted to man executed over M\u00e1m Trasna murders\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-04-04.</ref>\n* 6 April \u2013 [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC) lightweight champion [[Conor McGregor]] was charged with assault, menacing and reckless endangerment at the UFC 223 media day in [[New York City|New York]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/conor-mcgregor-charged-with-assault-in-new-york-36780607.html \"Conor McGregor charged with assault in New York\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-04-06.</ref>\n* 7 April \u2013 Up to 10,000 people took part in a demonstration in Dublin to demand action over the continuing housing crisis.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/thousands-march-in-protest-over-housing-crisis-836240.html \"Thousands march in protest over housing crisis\"], ''Irish Examiner'', 2018-04-07.</ref>\n* 9 April \u2013 Two American tourists died when a [[jaunting car]] overturned near the [[Gap of Dunloe]], [[County Kerry]].<ref>[https://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/two-us-tourists-die-in-freak-kerry-jaunting-car-accident-836466.html Two US tourists die in freak Kerry jaunting-car accident] Breaking News, 2018-04-09.</ref>\n* 10 April \u2013 \n**A man died after his fishing boat sank off the Mayo coast.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/connacht/2018/0410/953506-mayo-eagle-island/ Fisherman dies after boat sinks off Co Mayo coast] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-04-10.</ref>\n**Events were held in [[Belfast]] to mark the 20th anniversary of the [[Good Friday Agreement]].<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/timeline-how-the-good-friday-agreement-came-about-and-the-challenges-it-has-faced-since-36792676.html Timeline: How the Good Friday Agreement came about and the challenges it has faced since] Irish Independent, 2018-04-10.</ref>\n* 12 April \u2013 [[Eir (telecommunications)|Eir]] announced the loss of 750 jobs after a majority stake takeover by two French firms connected to a telecoms billionaire.<ref>[https://www.breakingnews.ie/business/eir-announces-the-loss-of-750-jobs-837042.html Eir announces the loss of 750 jobs] Breaking News, 2018-04-12.</ref>\n* 17 April \u2013 [[Enterprise Ireland]] launched \u20ac1 million for a competitive start fund for female entrepreneurs.<ref><enterprise-ireland-launches-e1-million-competitive-start-fund-for-female-entrepreneurs</ref>\n* 19 April \u2013 [[Minister for Communications, Climate Action and 