 counter water shortages\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-06-30.</ref>\n* 3 July \u2013 [[Ryanair]] pilots balloted by the Irish Air Line Pilots' Association voted in favour of a 24-hour strike on Thursday 12 July.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0703/975926-ryanair_pilots/ \"Irish-based Ryanair pilots to strike on 12 July\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-03.</ref>\n* 4 July \u2013 Irish Water announced that a nationwide hosepipe ban will be in effect from 8am on 6 July until midnight on 31 July as the dry spell continued across the country.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/heatwave/irish-water-confirms-nationwide-hosepipe-ban-will-come-into-effect-on-friday-37080221.html \"Irish Water confirms nationwide hosepipe ban will come into effect on Friday\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-07-04.</ref>\n* 5 July \u2013 26-year-old Hasan Bal from [[Waterford]] was sentenced to two-and-a-half years in prison for providing funding for the so-called [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/courts/2018/0705/976620-islamic-state-fundraiser-waterford/ \"Irish man jailed for providing funding for so-called Islamic State\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-05.</ref>\n* 6 July \u2013 The Road Traffic (Amendment) Bill was passed after heated exchanges in the D\u00e1il with 75 TDs voting in favour and eight TDs voting against.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/drink-driving-law-passed-in-d%C3%A1il-after-bitter-row-over-filibustering-1.3556181 \"Drink-driving law passed in D\u00e1il after bitter row over filibustering\"], ''Irish Times'', 2018-07-06.</ref>\n* 8 July \u2013 The National Day of Commemoration service took place at [[Collins Barracks, Dublin|Collins Barracks]], honouring Irish men and women who died in past wars or on United Nations service.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/national-day-of-commemoration-takes-place-at-dublins-collins-barracks-37092705.html \"National Day of Commemoration takes place at Dublin's Colli