</ref>\n* 13 July \n**County Clare-based diver Jim Warny, who was involved in the [[Tham Luang cave rescue|rescue of the Thai boys football team from a cave complex]], arrived back in Ireland.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0713/978435-thai-cave-rescue/ \"Clare-based diver welcomed home after Thai cave rescue\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-13.</ref>\n**D\u00e1il \u00c9ireann rose for the summer holidays which will last until 28 September.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2018/0712/978324-dail-summer-break/ \"D\u00e1il holidays begin but uncertainty remains\"], RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-13.</ref>\n**The Belfast homes of two prominent Sinn F\u00e9in members, Gerry Adams and [[Bobby Storey]], were attacked with explosive devices.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/gerry-adams-tells-those-who-attacked-his-home-to-explain-to-me-what-this-is-about-37117738.html Gerry Adams tells those who attacked his home to 'explain to me what this is about'] Irish Independent, 2018-07-14.</ref>\n[[File:Bray Head wildfire, 2018-07-13.jpg|thumb|right|Wildfire on Bray Head, 13 July]]\n** The July fire season resumed when an uncontrolled campfire at [[Bray Head]] began at 01:00 and spread over the hill, consuming [[Ulex|gorse]]. Homes were evacuated and train service halted while an [[Irish Air Corps|Air Corps]] [[AgustaWestland AW139|AW 139 helicopter]] lifted tonnes of water from [[Irish Sea|the sea]] to drown the blaze. Aerial operations were then suspended at 16:45 for some hours because of the danger posed to the helicopter by people flying [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|drones]] near the fire. Wicklow County Fire Service worked overnight and contained the fire. Before this operation, the Air Corps had already performed about 500 [[Helicopter bucket|water drops]] over wildfires in the previous fortnight, dropping more than 620,000 litres of water around the drought-ridden country.<ref>\n* [https://www.rte.ie/news/leinster/2018/0713/978402-bray-fire/ Houses evacuated as firefighters tackle Bray gorse fire] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-13.\n* [https://www.rte.ie/news/player/2018/0713/21399212-gorse-fire-on-bray-head-disrupts-rail-services/ Gorse fire on Bray Head disrupts rail services] RT\u00c9 News (video), 2018-07-13.\n* [https://twitter.com/IrishAirCorps/status/1017809546859941888 Anti-drone appeal] Irish Air Corps, 2018-07-13.\n* [https://twitter.com/DubFireBrigade/status/1017873937710149632 Camp fire warning] Dublin Fire Brigade, 2018-07-13.\n* [https://twitter.com/IrishAirCorps/status/1017484634622488576 600,000 litres of water dropped in 15 days] Irish Air Corps, 2018-07-12.\n* [https://www.rte.ie/news/leinster/2018/0714/978595-bray-head/ Firefighters contain gorse fire at Bray Head] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-07-14.\n* [https://www.rte.ie/news/player/2018/0714/21399315-firefighters-continue-to-battle-bray-gorse-fire/ Firefighters continue to battle Bray gorse fire] RT\u00c9 News (video), 2018-07-14.</ref>\n* 14 July \n**Sinn F\u00e9in announced that it is to contest the Presidential election, following a meeting of the party's Ard Comhairle.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/presidential-election-confirmed-as-sinn-fein-decide-to-field-candidate-37118402.html \"Presidential election confirmed as Sinn Fein decide to field candidate\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-07-14.</ref>\n**Minister for Foreign Affairs Simon Coveney and DUP leader Arlene Foster visited [[Derry]] following six successive nights of violence in the city.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/simon-coveney-and-arlene-foster-visit-derry-following-days-of-violence-37118909.html \"Simon Coveney and Arlene Foster visit Derry following days of violence\"], ''Irish Independent'', 2018-07-14.</ref>\n* 16 July \u2013 A megalithic passage tomb dating back some 5,500 years was discovered at the 18th century Dowth Hall in County Meath.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/leinster/2018/0716/979038-dowth-hall-meath-megalithic/ \"'Find of a lifetime' as Megalithic passage tomb discovered 