ish is spoken in the House of Commons for the first time in more than 100 years] Irish Times, 2018-10-23.</ref>\n* 26 October\n** The people of Ireland [[2018 Irish presidential election|voted]] to choose their president.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/0828/988011-presidential-election/ Presidential Election to be held on 26 October] RT\u00c9, 2018-08-28.</ref> \n** There was also a constitutional referendum to determine if the [[Blasphemy law in the Republic of Ireland|offence of blasphemy]] should be [[Thirty-seventh Amendment of the Constitution Bill 2018|removed from the Constitution]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/0612/970070-blasphemy/ Blasphemy referendum set to take place in October] RT\u00c9, 2018-06-12.</ref>\n* 27 October \u2013 Michael D. Higgins was officially declared President of Ireland after receiving 822,566 first preference votes.<ref>[https://www.thejournal.ie/irish-presidential-election-result-2018-4309332-Oct2018/ Michael D Higgins has been re-elected as President of Ireland with 55.8% of the vote] The Journal, 2018-10-27.</ref>\n* 31 October \n** It was announced that Garda whistleblower Maurice McCabe was retiring at midnight from an Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na after 30-year's of service.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/crime-and-law/garda-whistleblower-maurice-mccabe-to-retire-1.3681363 Garda whistleblower Maurice McCabe to retire] Irish Times, 2018-10-31.</ref>\n** Former Garda Commissioner [[N\u00f3ir\u00edn O'Sullivan]] was appointed as the United Nations' Assistant Secretary-General for Safety and Security.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2018/1031/1007845-noirin-osullivan/ N\u00f3ir\u00edn O'Sullivan appointed to UN role] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-10-31.</ref>\n\n===November===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 1 November \n** The [[Football Association of Ireland]] and the [[Irish Football Association]] launched a joint-bid to host the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2023 European Under-21 Championships]].<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/international/fai-and-ifa-confirm-joint-bid-to-host-2023-under-21-euros-1.3682836 FAI and IFA confirm joint bid to host 2023 Under-21 Euros] Irish Times, 2018-11-01.</ref> \n** Sinn F\u00e9in TD [[Peadar T\u00f3ib\u00edn]] was suspended from the party for six months after voting against abortion legislation.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/1101/1007991-td-suspension/ TD Peadar T\u00f3ib\u00edn suspended from Sinn F\u00e9in over abortion vote] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-11-01.</ref>\n** Staff at [[Google]] offices around the world, including Dublin, staged an unprecedented series of walkouts in protest at the company's treatment of women.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/google-staff-in-dublin-join-international-walkout-in-protest-over-sexual-harassment-claims-37481871.html Google staff in Dublin join international walkout in protest over sexual harassment claims] Irish Independent, 2018-11-01.</ref>\n* 2 November \u2013 Jonathan Keogh, Thomas Fox and Regina Keogh were each given life sentences after being found guilty of murdering Gareth Hutch in May 2016.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/courts/2018/1102/1008229-gareth-hutch-courts/ Three given life sentences for murder of Gareth Hutch in 2016] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-11-02.</ref>\n* 3 November \u2013 [[Irish Labour Party|Labour Party]] leader [[Brendan Howlin]] called on his party's voters to also lend support to some other parties and progressive independents at the [[Next Irish general election|next election]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2018/1103/1008479-labour-conference/ Labour calls on voters to also support select parties and 'progressive independents'] RT\u00c9 News, 2018-11-03.</ref>\n* 4 November \u2013 Hundreds of people attended an event in [[St. Stephen's Green]] to mark the arrival of a six-metre-high ({{convert|6|m|ft|disp=out}}) sculpture of a [[World War I]] soldier.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com