3687.html|title=Irish athletics star (33) dies in car crash in South Carolina|work=Irish Independent}}</ref>\n* 19 February \u2013 [[Catherine Nevin]], 67, convicted murderer, brain tumour.<ref name=\"CatherineNevin NewsTalk\">{{cite news|title=Convicted Murderer Catherine Nevin dies age 67|url=http://www.newstalk.com/Convicted-murderer-Catherine-Nevin-dies-aged-67|accessdate=20 February 2018|newspaper=[[Newstalk]]|date=20 February 2018}}</ref>\n* 20 February  \n** Brendan Heneghan, 53, Fine Gael politician and businessman, heart attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/politics/i-will-miss-him-greatly-enda-kenny-leads-tributes-after-sudden-death-of-political-ally-36623120.html|title='I will miss him greatly' - Enda Kenny leads tributes after sudden death of political ally|work=Irish Independent}}</ref>\n** [[Frank Norberg]], 69, hurler ([[Cork GAA|Cork]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blackrockhurlingclub.com/2018/02/20/frank-norberg-rip/|title=Frank Norberg RIP}}</ref>\n* 28 February \u2013 [[Kieron Durkan]], 44, footballer ([[Republic of Ireland national under-21 football team|national under-21 team]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/semi-pro-footballer-who-scored-14353227|title=Semi-pro footballer who scored against Manchester United found dead in car|first=Connor|last=Dunn|date=1 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n[[File:Liam O'Flinn.jpg|thumb|right|120px|[[Liam O'Flynn]]]]\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED -->\n* 3 March \n** [[Emma Hannigan]], 45, author, cancer.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2018/0303/944778-irish-writer-emma-hannigan-dies-after-cancer-battle/ Irish writer Emma Hannigan dies after 11-year cancer battle], rte.ie</ref>\n** Fred Perry, 84, businessman and golf official, road traffic collision.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/regionals/sligochampion/news/sadness-at-death-of-former-boyle-store-owner-in-collision-36670212.html Sadness at death of former 