{"title_page": "The Strong, Silent Type", "text_new": "{{Infobox Television episode\n| title          = The Strong, Silent Type\n| series         = [[The Sopranos]]\n| caption        = Paulie confronts Christopher at an intervention for Christopher\u2019s heroin use.\n| season         = 4\n| episode        = 10\n| guests         = ''see below''\n| airdate        = November 17, 2002\n| length         = 53 minutes\n| editor         = \n| production     = 410\n| teleplay       = {{Unbulleted list|[[Terence Winter]]|[[Robin Green]]|[[Mitchell Burgess]]}}\n| story          = [[David Chase]]\n| director       = [[Alan Taylor (director)|Alan Taylor]]\n| photographer   = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list   = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 4)\n| image          = Sopranos_ep410.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| prev           = [[Whoever Did This]]\n| next           = [[Calling All Cars (The Sopranos)|Calling All Cars]]\n}}\n\"'''The Strong, Silent Type'''\" is the 49th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the 10th of the show's fourth season. Its teleplay was written by [[Terence Winter]], [[Robin Green]], and [[Mitchell Burgess]] from a story by [[David Chase]]. It was directed by [[Alan Taylor (director)|Alan Taylor]] and originally aired on November 17, 2002.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] \n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]] *\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]] *\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Vincent Curatola]] as [[Johnny Sack]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]] *\n\n''* = credit only''\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Tom Aldredge]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Hugh De Angelis|Hugh De Angelis]] \n* [[Sharon Angela]] as [[Rosalie Aprile]] \n* [[Leslie Bega]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Valentina La Paz|Valentina La Paz]]\n* [[Carl Capotorto]] as [[Little Paulie Germani]] \n* [[Max Casella]] as [[Benny Fazio]]\n* Dane Curley as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Justin Cifaretto|Justin Cifaretto]]\n* [[Joseph R. Gannascoli]] as [[Vito Spatafore]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* [[Alla Kliouka Schaffer]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana Kirilenko]]\n* [[Elias Koteas]] as Dominic Palladino\n* [[Marianne Leone Cooper|Marianne Leone]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Joanne Moltisanti|Joanne Moltisanti]]\n* Richard Maldone as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert \"Ally Boy\" Barese|Ally Boy Barese]]\n* Marissa Matrone as Ronnie Capozza \n* [[Arthur J. Nascarella]] as [[Carlo Gervasi]]\n* [[Suzanne Shepherd]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Mary Pellegrino De Angelis|Mary De Angelis]] \n* [[Maureen Van Zandt]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Gabriella Dante|Gabriella Dante]] \n* [[Karen Young (actress)|Karen Young]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Sanseverino]]\n* Frank Santorelli as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#George .22Georgie.22 Santorelli|Georgie]]\n* Elena Solovey as Branca Libinsk\n* [[Daniel London]] as Eddie\n* Herman Chavez as Street Punk\n* Carlos Pizarro as Drug Dealer\n* Cristina Ablaza as Doctor\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\nA week after [[Ralph Cifaretto|Ralphie]]'s \"disappearance\", there is still no word of him. At a dinner with [[Silvio Dante|Silvio]] and [[Patsy Parisi|Patsy]], [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert \"Ally Boy\" Barese|Albert]] voices the crew's suspicions that Tony killed Ralphie because of a horse. At a meeting, [[Johnny Sack|Johnny]] demands that Tony let [[Lupertazzi crime family|New York]] in on the [[United States Department of Housing and Urban Development|HUD]] scam. When Tony refuses, Johnny threatens him. Tony calls a meeting of key family members, and asserts that Johnny had Ralphie killed over the HUD scam. He stresses that no action should be taken until they have proof.\n\nAt a session with [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr. Melfi]] Tony tearfully expresses his pain over losing [[Pie-O-My]], and Melfi comments that he seems to grieve more for animals than for humans. The portrait of him and the horse is delivered to the [[Bada Bing]]; Tony orders it destroyed. But when Paulie sees [[Benny Fazio|Benny]] and [[Little Paulie Germani|Little Paulie]] trying to burn the painting he rescues it, over-valuing it and saying it would be an honor to have it in his house. He hangs it in his living room, but later takes it down to have it modified to garb Tony in a \"[[Napoleon Bonaparte|Napoleon]]-like\" uniform. He  hangs it up again and sits with his back to it while watching television, but Tony's eyes are still on him.\n\n[[Furio Giunta|Furio]] returns, with gifts for [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] and [[Meadow Soprano|Meadow]] but, to her disappointment, nothing for [[Carmela Soprano|Carmela]]. He still declines to enter the house with her. She again finds a pretext to visit him at his home, again taking her unwilling chaperone A.J., who is beginning to understand the situation. Carmela confides in [[Rosalie Aprile|Rosalie]], who urges her not to go any further with Furio; they both know what Tony would do if he found out.\n\nTony admires [[Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana]], who has established her own nurses' agency, which supplies the nurse assigned to [[Junior Soprano|Junior]]. When the nurse is ill, Svetlana takes her place. Tony goes to the house one afternoon when he knows Junior is napping.  They have sex on Junior's couch. Afterwards, Tony is put out when she suggests they not see each other again. The regular nurse returns unexpectedly and can tell what has been going on. \n\n[[Adriana La Cerva|Adriana]] breaks down in tears when she finds that [[Christopher Moltisanti|Christopher]], in a [[heroin]]-induced stupor, sat on her dog and killed it. Her [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] handler, Agent [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Sanseverino]], says Adriana should urge him to go into [[Drug rehabilitation|rehab]], and she has arranged for material to be sent to their home. Chris is [[carjacked]], robbed, and beaten up while attempting to purchase heroin in a low-income [[barrio]]. When he returns home, Adriana gives him a pamphlet for a rehab clinic. He is infuriated and hits her.\n\nBadly bruised, Adriana goes to Carmela. Junior advises Tony to kill Chris, but he cannot do it. Instead, family and friends organize an [[intervention (counseling)|intervention]]. It soon degenerates. Tony is enraged when he hears that Chris killed Adriana's dog. Chris verbally attacks those trying to help him and insults [[List of characters from The Sopranos - friends and family#Joanne Blundetto Moltisanti|his own mother]]. The men turn on him and beat him up. The intervention ends with Chris being taken to the emergency room with a [[hairline fracture|hairline skull fracture]]. Tony arranges for him to go to a rehab clinic in [[Pennsylvania]] and demands that he not leave until he is clean, telling him that [[Patsy Parisi|Patsy]] will be watching him.\n\n==Deceased==\n* '''Cosette''': killed when Christopher, high on heroin, sits on her while she was lying on a sofa. Cosette appears in a dream sequence in the season 6 episode [[Cold Stones]].\n\n==Production==\n* Carmela ([[Edie Falco]]) sports a new, shorter hairdo beginning with this episode.\n\n==Title reference==\n* The episode's title refers to [[Gary Cooper]], who Tony has described as a perfect model of a man. Tony mentions Cooper several times during the series, describing him as \"the strong, silent type\". He first said it during therapy in the [[Pilot (The Sopranos)|series pilot]], and again in the 4th season episode \"[[Christopher (The Sopranos)|Christopher]].\" The concept finds value in strength through keeping silent, an American model of Omert\u00e0.\n\n==Other cultural references==\n* At the start of the episode, as Christopher gets high on heroin before sitting on the dog, Cosette, the television was showing an ''[[Our Gang]]'' short film ''[[Bear Shooters]]''.\n* When Adriana comes home Christopher is asleep in front of the TV, on which the 1966 movie ''[[The Oscar (film)|The Oscar]]'' is being shown.\n* Paulie tells Silvio he watched ''[[On the Waterfront]]'' in HD and was impressed, saying \"[[Karl Malden]]'s nose hairs looked like [[power cable|BX cables]]\".\n* The baseball game Paulie watches near the end of the episode is a [[Boston Red Sox]]-[[New York Yankees]] game played at [[Yankee Stadium (1923)|Yankee Stadium]] on September 4, 2002, and won by the Yankees, 3-1. The play shown is Yankee [[designated hitter]] [[Jason Giambi]]'s fourth-inning two-run home run off Red Sox starter [[Derek Lowe]]. Then-Red Sox left fielder [[Rickey Henderson]] is also referred to by the game's announcer.\n* When Carmela and AJ are at Furio's house, AJ is wearing a [[Soulfly]] T-shirt.\n\n==Music==\n* When Adriana is talking to the FBI agent, the other car stereo is playing the song \"Analyse\" by [[The Cranberries]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hbo.com/the-sopranos/episodes/index.html#/the-sopranos/episodes/4/49-the-strong-silent-type/index.html \"The Strong, Silent Type\"] at [[HBO]]\n*{{imdb episode|0705283}}\n*{{tv.com episode|the-sopranos/the-strong-silent-type-200400}}\n\n{{The Sopranos}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Strong, Silent Type, The}}\n[[Category:The Sopranos (season 4) episodes]]\n[[Category:2002 American television episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Television episode\n| title          = The Strong, Silent Type\n| series         = [[The Sopranos]]\n| caption        = Paulie confronts Christopher at the intervention for Christopher\u2019s heroin use.\n| season         = 4\n| episode        = 10\n| guests         = ''see below''\n| airdate        = November 17, 2002\n| length         = 53 minutes\n| editor         = \n| production     = 410\n| teleplay       = {{Unbulleted list|[[Terence Winter]]|[[Robin Green]]|[[Mitchell Burgess]]}}\n| story          = [[David Chase]]\n| director       = [[Alan Taylor (director)|Alan Taylor]]\n| photographer   = [[Alik Sakharov]]\n| episode_list   = List of The Sopranos episodes\n| season_article = The Sopranos (season 4)\n| image          = Sopranos_ep410.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| prev           = [[Whoever Did This]]\n| next           = [[Calling All Cars (The Sopranos)|Calling All Cars]]\n}}\n\"'''The Strong, Silent Type'''\" is the 49th episode of the [[HBO]] original series ''[[The Sopranos]]'' and the 10th of the show's fourth season. Its teleplay was written by [[Terence Winter]], [[Robin Green]], and [[Mitchell Burgess]] from a story by [[David Chase]]. It was directed by [[Alan Taylor (director)|Alan Taylor]] and originally aired on November 17, 2002.\n\n==Starring==\n* [[James Gandolfini]] as [[Tony Soprano]]\n* [[Lorraine Bracco]] as [[Dr. Jennifer Melfi]] \n* [[Edie Falco]] as [[Carmela Soprano]]\n* [[Michael Imperioli]] as [[Christopher Moltisanti]]\n* [[Dominic Chianese]] as [[Junior Soprano|Corrado Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Steven Van Zandt]] as [[Silvio Dante]]\n* [[Tony Sirico]] as [[Paulie Gualtieri]]\n* [[Robert Iler]] as [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.]] \n* [[Jamie-Lynn Sigler]] as [[Meadow Soprano]] *\n* [[Drea de Matteo]] as [[Adriana La Cerva]]\n* [[Aida Turturro]] as [[Janice Soprano]] *\n* [[Federico Castelluccio]] as [[Furio Giunta]]\n* [[Vincent Curatola]] as [[Johnny Sack]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as [[Ralph Cifaretto]] *\n\n''* = credit only''\n\n===Guest starring===\n{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Tom Aldredge]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Hugh De Angelis|Hugh De Angelis]] \n* [[Sharon Angela]] as [[Rosalie Aprile]] \n* [[Leslie Bega]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Valentina La Paz|Valentina La Paz]]\n* [[Carl Capotorto]] as [[Little Paulie Germani]] \n* [[Max Casella]] as [[Benny Fazio]]\n* Dane Curley as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Justin Cifaretto|Justin Cifaretto]]\n* [[Joseph R. Gannascoli]] as [[Vito Spatafore]]\n* [[Dan Grimaldi]] as [[Patsy Parisi]]\n* [[Alla Kliouka Schaffer]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Svetlana Kirilenko|Svetlana Kirilenko]]\n* [[Elias Koteas]] as Dominic Palladino\n* [[Marianne Leone Cooper|Marianne Leone]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Joanne Moltisanti|Joanne Moltisanti]]\n* Richard Maldone as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert \"Ally Boy\" Barese|Ally Boy Barese]]\n* Marissa Matrone as Ronnie Capozza \n* [[Arthur J. Nascarella]] as [[Carlo Gervasi]]\n* [[Suzanne Shepherd]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Mary Pellegrino De Angelis|Mary De Angelis]] \n* [[Maureen Van Zandt]] as [[List of characters from The Sopranos - Friends and Family#Gabriella Dante|Gabriella Dante]] \n* [[Karen Young (actress)|Karen Young]] as [[FBI on The Sopranos#Agent Robyn Sanseverino|Agent Sanseverino]]\n* Frank Santorelli as [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#George .22Georgie.22 Santorelli|Georgie]]\n* Elena Solovey as Branca Libinsk\n* [[Daniel London]] as Eddie\n* Herman Chavez as Street Punk\n* Carlos Pizarro as Drug Dealer\n* Cristina Ablaza as Doctor\n}}\n\n==Synopsis==\nA week after [[Ralph Cifaretto|Ralphie]]'s \"disappearance\", there is still no word of him. At a dinner with [[Silvio Dante|Silvio]] and [[Patsy Parisi|Patsy]], [[List of characters from The Sopranos in the Soprano crime family#Albert \"Ally Boy\" Barese|Albert]] voices the crew's suspicions that Tony killed Ralphie because of a horse. At a meeting, [[Johnny Sack|Johnny]] demands that Tony let [[Lupertazzi crime family|New York]] in on the [[United States Department of Housing and Urban Development|HUD]] scam. When Tony refuses, Johnny threatens him. Tony calls a meeting of key family members, and asserts that Johnny had Ralphie killed over the HUD scam. He stresses that no action should be taken until they have proof.\n\nAt a session with [[Jennifer Melfi|Dr. Melfi]] Tony tearfully expresses his pain over losing [[Pie-O-My]], and Melfi comments that he seems to grieve more for animals than for humans. The portrait of him and the horse is delivered to the [[Bada Bing]]; Tony orders it destroyed. But when Paulie sees [[Benny Fazio|Benny]] and [[Little Paulie Germani|Little Paulie]] trying to burn the painting he rescues it, over-valuing it and saying it would be an honor to have it in his house. He hangs it in his living room, but later takes it down to have it modified to garb Tony in a \"[[Napoleon Bonaparte|Napoleon]]-like\" uniform. He  hangs it up again and sits with his back to it while watching television, but Tony's eyes are still on him.\n\n[[Furio Giunta|Furio]] returns, with gifts for [[Anthony Soprano, Jr.|A.J.]] and [[Meadow Soprano|Meadow]] but, to her disappointment, nothing for [[Carmela Soprano|Carmela]]. He still declines to enter the house with her. She again finds a pretext to visit him at his home, again taking her unwilling chaperone A.J., who is beginning to understand the situation. Carmela confides in [[Rosalie Aprile|Rosalie]], who urges her not to go any further with Furio; they both know what Tony would do if he found out.\n\nTony ad